review_blob: A simple beer, albeit flavorful. Highly drinkable with a little personality--not too bitter, not too sweet--with little to no aftertaste. Turned me on to Napa Smith at large for trying other of the brands beers. Wen exceptionally well with a chicken salad panini.
beer_name: Napa Ale Works All Malt Red Ale

full body, black, heavy cloying sweetness.

Very rich, thick, moms favorite beer. Pricey, comes in four-pack. Robust and drinkable.
